<br>
i am level 30 and have 147wis. kiting is SLOW and very boring at my level (hell level i hear) and i want more mana so i can get maybe 3 kites per mana dump instead of my current 2. i can not multi kite with much success at this level but what i can do is snare, root, dot, and med. this is good for 2 kills per use of all my mana. then i have to med up. <br>
<br>
if i can get more mana i might be able to get 3 kites per mana dump. because its hard finding good crack, and i don't like to beg so i am usually crackless.<br>
<br>
so to make this long post longer, would someone be so kind as to give me a list of some items i might be able to purchase at kelethin auction or whatever that will boost my wis a nice amount?<br>
<br>
i am at work so i dunno if this is exact, but here's what i have currently.<br>
<br>
head - savents cap +3 wis i think<br>
neck - no wis leather<br>
ears - left +2 wis electrum  right +3 wis jade i think<br>
face - no wis leather<br>
shoulders - some kind of magic pads +4 wis<br>
chest - foremans tunic<br>
arms - good arm item +6 wis i think, forgot its name<br>
leggs - leather<br>
belt - 10ac no wis bonus<br>
boots - leather<br>
wrists - bracer of battle and leather so no wis bonus<br>
secondary slot - testament of vanear +10 wis +10 mana<br>
primary - screaming mace<br>
ranged - split paw gem or something, sv poison<br>
<br>
with tis in mind, whats obtainable to really help a druid out with a lack of mana? neck, leggs, feet, wrists, and face most desired. i am looking for a runed circlet, i think they drop in everfrost someplace but i'd gladly pay for one on povar send me a tell /tell draviss<br>
<br>
thank you!!!<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/15/01 7:26:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 30 and want more mana! want help pls!</span><hr size=1> Ok...since you did not list your current $ situation, I will list the prices of the items next to them.<br>
<br>
Head-Runed Circlet(?ac, 4wis/int) 200-400pp<br>
Neck-Blackened Iron Medalion (3wis/int) 20pp max<br>
Ears-Get another +3 wis (20pp?), or go hunt giants in FM and hope to get yourself some forest loops<br>
Face-Silver ruby veil (4wis/str) 200pp, Plat ruby veil (7wis/str) 600pp, Vel Ruby veil (8wis/str) 800-1k<br>
Shoulders-Braided Ivy chords (4ac 5wis) 500pp max, should be able to camp the browny that drops these in lfay<br>
Chest-Formans is just fine, might want to consider an Ulthork Hide tunic (13ac, 3wis, 35man, -35hp, -? charisma) 1k max<br>
Legs-Gator Legs (7ac 4wis 15hp) 700-1k, or if you can't afford those, Black Chiten legs (7ac 10hp, 25(?) mana) 500pp max<br>
Arms- +6wis???? well...I kinda doubt that it is +6wis (unless it is some uber arm I have never heard of), but I am guessing you have a plat arm band (3wis/str) that is just fine<br>
Belt- Straw Spun belt you have is just fine, or if you have the pp get a crystaline belt (not sure on stats, all I know is 3wis) 1500pp<br>
Wrists-Polished Bone Bracers (3wis/int ?ac) 150pp for a pair, or chipped bone bracers (?ac 5wis) 800-1k for a pair<br>
Secondary-Testament is just fine, if you have the pp, a charred guardian sheild is nice (10ac 9wis) 500pp<br>
Primary-no wis, but get a runed falchion, get your 1hs skill up, the epic is 1hs :) 500pp or so, keep that till you can finish the paw quest at about 35, then put it in a backpack<br>
Range-Split paw eye just fine, if u have the pp get a totem of the warrior spirit (3wis/str 10hp range) 2k<br>
Rings-you didn't mention these, but if you don't already have some, get some plat jasper or vel jasper rings (6wis/7wis respectavely) 400pp pair for plat, 1k for vel<br>
Like I said, I have no idea how much money you have to spend, but I think I have given a pretty good baseline for what you can shoot for. Sorry for the length of this post.<br>
